 {"id":"franken_networkx-fdsn","title":"parity: conversion live views adj should preserve atlas-view mapping helpers","description":"The top-level to_directed(...) and to_undirected(...) live views currently expose adj mapping helpers whose values are internal _ConversionNeighborMap objects in FrankenNetworkX. list(view.adj.items()) and list(view.adj.values()) therefore return implementation-specific wrappers instead of the AtlasView-style mapping values NetworkX exposes. Match the upstream adj mapping-helper contract on conversion live views.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:34:39.175225125Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T09:34:39.175225125Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-fdu5","title":"parity: reverse_view should expose NodeView object on nodes","description":"reverse_view(...) currently exposes .nodes as a bound method instead of NetworkX's NodeView object. In FrankenNetworkX, type(reverse_view(G).nodes).__name__ is 'method' and helpers like reverse_view(G).nodes.data() / .items() fail immediately, while upstream NetworkX exposes a callable NodeView object. Match the upstream reverse_view .nodes contract.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:03:46.057874208Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T09:05:19.084912090Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}

